# The `Graph` Class Template Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/graph">Graph</a> object represents a Directed <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/graph">Graph</a> and is used in XRay to compute and store function call graphs and associated statistical information. <a href="#details">More...</a>

<CodeBlock>template &lt;typename VertexAttribute, typename EdgeAttribute, typename VI = int32&#95;t&gt;

## Description {#details}

A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/graph">Graph</a> object represents a Directed <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/graph">Graph</a> and is used in XRay to compute and store function call graphs and associated statistical information.

The graph takes in four template parameters, these are:
<ul>
<li>VertexAttribute, this is a structure which is stored for each vertex. Must be DefaultConstructible, CopyConstructible, CopyAssignable and Destructible.</li>
<li>EdgeAttribute, this is a structure which is stored for each edge Must be DefaultConstructible, CopyConstructible, CopyAssignable and Destructible.</li>
<li>EdgeAttribute, this is a structure which is stored for each variable</li>
<li>VI, this is a type over which <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/densemapinfo">DenseMapInfo</a> is defined and is the type used look up strings, available as <a href="#aa7d4f1e9198ebd47ab0fc3cef797ac86">VertexIdentifier</a>.</li>
<li>If the built in <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/densemapinfo">DenseMapInfo</a> is not defined, provide a specialization class type here.</li>
</ul>


<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/graph">Graph</a> is CopyConstructible, CopyAssignable, MoveConstructible and MoveAssignable but is not EqualityComparible or LessThanComparible.

Usage Example <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/graph">Graph</a> with weighted edges and vertices: <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/graph">Graph&lt;int, int, int&gt;</a> G;

G&#91;1&#93; = 0; G&#91;2&#93; = 2; G&#91;&#123;1,2&#125;&#93; = 1; G&#91;&#123;2,1&#125;&#93; = -1; for(const auto &amp;v : G.vertices())&#123; // Do something with the vertices in the graph; &#125; for(const auto &amp;e : G.edges())&#123; // Do something with the edges in the graph; &#125;

Usage Example with StrRef keys. <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/xray/graph">Graph&lt;int, double, StrRef&gt;</a> StrG; char va&#91;&#93; = &quot;Vertex A&quot;; char vaa&#91;&#93; = &quot;Vertex A&quot;; char vb&#91;&#93; = &quot;Vertex B&quot;; // Vertices are referenced by String Refs. G&#91;va&#93; = 0; G&#91;vb&#93; = 1; G&#91;&#123;va, vb&#125;&#93; = 1.0; cout() &lt;&lt; G&#91;vaa&#93; &lt;&lt; &quot; &quot; &lt;&lt; G&#91;&#123;vaa, vb&#125;&#93;; //prints &quot;0 1.0&quot;.
